SIMPLE: forgetful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forgetful
<hw>For*get"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Apt to
forget; easily losing remembrance; <as>as, a <ex>forgetful</ex> man
should use helps to strengthen his memory</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Heedless; careless; neglectful;
inattentive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be not <qex>forgetful</qex> to entertain strangers.</q>
<rj><qau>Heb. xiii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Causing to forget; inducing oblivion;
oblivious.</def> <mark>[Archaic or Poetic]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>forgetful</xex> wine.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. Webster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forgetfully</ent>⟦br⟧
